
- *Cross-disease HSAT2 comparison framework* ([Chapter 14d, new Section; Chapter 20, HSAT2 section expanded; Appendix H, 7 new annotated entries; references.bib, 7 new entries; hypothesis-registry.typ, 9 new entries]): Comparative framework for HSAT2 retrotransposon activation across ME/CFS, Long COVID, cancer, and fibrotic diseases. Added cross-disease evidence table to Ch14d showing HSAT2 validation status (high in cancer, HERV data in COVID-19, absent in fibrotic/post-viral conditions). Added pan-retrotransposon stress response hypothesis to Ch14d proposing disease-specific kinetics patterns (progressive in cancer vs plateaued in post-viral syndromes). Added EBV/CMV subset driver speculation to Ch14d. Added HSAT2 kinetic distinction hypothesis to Ch14d. Added multi-modal diagnostic panel proposal to Ch20. Added exosomal HSAT2 tissue origin open question, fibrotic disease HSAT2 gap speculation, HSAT2 methylation lock speculation, cross-disease HSAT2 network analysis proposal, and retrotransposon-induced autoimmunity speculation to Ch14d. Updated hypothesis registry with 9 new entries. _Motivated by:_ @Seimiya2023HSATII — serum HSATII RNA as pancreatic cancer biomarker; @Yoruker2026HSAT2cfDNA — plasma cfDNA HSAT2 as colon cancer biomarker; @Evdokimova2019HSAT2exosome — exosomal HSAT2/HERV-K immune suppression mechanism; @Grandi2023HERVcovid — HERV transcriptome dynamics in COVID-19; @Charvet2023HERV — SARS-CoV-2 awakens ancient retroviral genes with HERV-W ENV correlation to severity.

	- *Vascular inflammation in neuropsychiatric Long COVID integration* ([Chapter 14k, 3 new hypothesis environments, 2 new speculation environments, 4 new open-question environments; mathematical model with limitation environment; Appendix H, 1 new annotated entry; references.bib, 1 new entry; hypothesis-registry.typ, 4 new entries]): Integration of McAlpine et al. 2026 vascular biomarker study demonstrating endothelial dysfunction WITHOUT overt coagulopathy in Long COVID, with cognitive and psychiatric symptom correlations. Added novel hypotheses extending Long COVID findings to ME/CFS: endothelial adhesion-cognition correlation (0.40), AGP neuroprotective biomarker speculation (0.25), vascular biomarker temporal evolution model (0.35). Added treatment proposals: anti-adhesion therapy for cognitive symptoms, biomarker-guided ME/CFS subtype stratification. Added formal limitation environment to speculative mathematical model. Fixed citation keys to use correct bib entries. Corrected ADAMTS13 classification error (VWF-cleaving protease, not endothelial adhesion molecule). Updated hypothesis registry with 4 new entries. _Motivated by:_ @McAlpine2026 — vascular inflammation correlates with cognitive/psychiatric symptoms in Long COVID; endothelial dysfunction distinction from coagulopathy; cross-disease mechanistic parallels with ME/CFS.
